===Openness in science===

fields listed as in <ref>[http://opensourcecognitivescience.wordpress.com/2009/08/04/kinds-of-openness-in-cognitive-science/ Kinds of openness in cognitive science] [http://opensourcecognitivescience.wordpress.com/about/ Mark Tovey], 4 August 2009 :</ref>

#[[Open Access]], where publications are made available on the web without charge
#Open Courseware is a movement that invites educators to make their course-material directly available on the web
#[[Open Source Hardware]] and [[Open Source Software]], where plans for apparatus and tools for analysis are made freely and openly available
#[[Open Stimuli]], where stimulus sets or corpi are made available for use in replications or new experiments
#[[Open Workflow]]s, in which researchers can freely share chains of experimentation, analysis, and visualization
#[[Open Data]], where individual researchers release their datasets, either as the data is collected, upon publication, or after a suitable embargo period
#[[Open Model Repositories]], where computational models from published papers can be centralized
#[[Open Research]], where open lab notebooks are used to describe ongoing details of a particular strain of research.

